{"article_id":"jvelz0HuxsTeR6AK","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"Gallup poll shows","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"majority of Americans think","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"Barack Obama will win re-election","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"National polls show","depth":6},{"id":5,"text":"that the race is pretty much a dead heat","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"Numbers behind the overall results show","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Obama is at tipping point among white voters","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"Romney campaign points to Obama polling below 50 %","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"-- a make or break line for incumbents","depth":7},{"id":10,"text":"A majority of Americans think","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"President Barack Obama will win re-election ,","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"according to a Gallup poll on Wednesday .","depth":7},{"id":13,"text":"By a 54 % -34 % margin , the public thinks","depth":7},{"id":14,"text":"Obama will defeat Republican nominee Mitt Romney on November 6 .","depth":7},{"id":15,"text":"But the actual race for the White House appears to be a much , much closer contest .","depth":6},{"id":16,"text":"National surveys of those likely to vote in the presidential contest","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"indicate","depth":9},{"id":18,"text":"the race is basically tied ,","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"with surveys in the crucial battleground states suggesting","depth":11},{"id":20,"text":"that Obama has the slightest of edges over his GOP challenger .","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"A CNN Poll of Polls ,","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"which averages the eight live operator , non-partisan , national surveys of likely voters","depth":11},{"id":23,"text":"conducted over the past nine days","depth":12},{"id":24,"text":"( nearly entirely after the final presidential debate )","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"indicates Romney at 48 % and the president at 47 % .","depth":9},{"id":26,"text":"But it 's the numbers behind the topline figures","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"that tell the real story .","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"And one of them is race .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"`` I think","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"what we 're really seeing in the national polling is that the president is right at the do-or-die line among white voters , ''","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"said CNN Senior Political Analyst and National Journal Editorial Director Ron Brownstein .","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"Brownstein says","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"that Obama needs to carry 40 % of the white vote and 80 % of the minority vote","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"to win a second term .","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"JUST WATCHED Ohio votes crucial for both campaigns","depth":7},{"id":36,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":37,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":7},{"id":38,"text":"Ohio votes crucial for both campaigns","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"03:34","depth":8},{"id":40,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":41,"text":"What do the latest campaign polls mean ?","depth":10},{"id":42,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":43,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"What do the latest campaign polls mean ?","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"08:12","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"JUST WATCHED Voter enthusiasm key to turnout","depth":7},{"id":47,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":7},{"id":48,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"Voter enthusiasm key to turnout","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"04:48","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"While the national polls are revealing ,","depth":5},{"id":52,"text":"the race for the White House is a battle for the states and their electoral votes ,","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"with 270 being the magic number .","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"The contest will be won or lost in the battleground states","depth":6},{"id":55,"text":"and no state is getting more attention than Ohio ,","depth":9},{"id":56,"text":"where 18 electoral votes are up for grabs .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"A CNN Poll of Polls","depth":12},{"id":58,"text":"that averages the five non-partisan , live operator surveys","depth":13},{"id":59,"text":"conducted in Ohio","depth":14},{"id":60,"text":"following last week 's debate","depth":14},{"id":61,"text":"indicates Obama at 49 % and Romney at 46 % among likely voters in the Buckeye State .","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"No Republican in modern times has won the White House","depth":11},{"id":63,"text":"without carrying Ohio .","depth":11},{"id":64,"text":"While the latest public opinion polls give Obama the slight edge ,","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"the Romney campaign remains confident .","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"`` We believe","depth":13},{"id":67,"text":"we can and will win Ohio .","depth":13},{"id":68,"text":"I think","depth":13},{"id":69,"text":"many of these polls","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"if you take them together","depth":17},{"id":71,"text":"and average them ,","depth":17},{"id":72,"text":"the trend line has been in our favor","depth":16},{"id":73,"text":"and the race in Ohio is very close , ''","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"Romney campaign spokesman Kevin Madden told reporters on Wednesday .","depth":11},{"id":75,"text":"The swing state of Virginia 's also getting a ton of attention .","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"A CNN Poll of Polls","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"that averages the four non-partisan , live operator surveys","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"conducted in Virginia since the debate","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"indicates Romney at 48 % and Obama at 47 % .","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"And in Florida , a CBS News/New York Times/Quinnipiac University poll also indicates a race","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"that 's tied up ,","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"with the president at 48 % and Romney at 47 % .","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"A CNN/ORC International poll","depth":13},{"id":84,"text":"released Monday","depth":13},{"id":85,"text":"also showed","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"the race for Florida 's 29 electoral votes deadlocked with Romney at 50 % and Obama at 49 % .","depth":11},{"id":87,"text":"The Obama campaign likes the numbers","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"coming out of the public opinion polls in the swing states .","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"`` We feel very very good about the numbers","depth":10},{"id":90,"text":"that we 're mounting up in those states , ''","depth":10},{"id":91,"text":"Obama campaign senior adviser David Axelrod told reporters on Wednesday .","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"`` We 're maintaining double-digit leads among women , ''","depth":9},{"id":93,"text":"added Axelrod ,","depth":10},{"id":94,"text":"discussing the all-important and much-discussed female vote .","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"The Romney campaign also says","depth":9},{"id":96,"text":"it 's in a very good place with a week to go .","depth":9},{"id":97,"text":"`` This race is exactly where we had hoped","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"it would be a week out .","depth":10},{"id":99,"text":"It is a close race , ''","depth":11},{"id":100,"text":"said senior Romney adviser Russ Schriefer on a conference call on Wednesday .","depth":11},{"id":101,"text":"`` We have an incumbent president","depth":13},{"id":102,"text":"that is stuck well below the 50 % threshold in almost every mark","depth":15},{"id":103,"text":"that you can take ,","depth":15},{"id":104,"text":"whether it 's the national polls or the state polls .","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"And","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"as you know ,","depth":15},{"id":107,"text":"under 50 % , or well under 50 % is not a very happy place to be","depth":15},{"id":108,"text":"if you are an incumbent a week out , ''","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"Schriefer added .","depth":11},{"id":110,"text":"Most news organizations ,","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"including CNN ,","depth":11},{"id":112,"text":"rate Pennsylvania as a `` lean-Obama '' state .","depth":10},{"id":113,"text":"But a Franklin and Marshall College poll","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"released Wednesday","depth":13},{"id":115,"text":"indicates Obama with a 49 % -45 % advantage over Romney ,","depth":12},{"id":116,"text":"which is within the survey 's sampling error","depth":12},{"id":117,"text":"and is down from a nine-point lead","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"he had last month .","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"The new Franklin and Marshall poll is the fifth non-partisan , live operator survey","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"released this month in Pennsylvania","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"to indicate a close contest for the state 's 20 electoral votes .","depth":11},{"id":122,"text":"The Romney campaign and its allies are going up with ad buys in the Keystone State as well as Minnesota and Michigan , two other states","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"that have been shaded blue in recent cycles .","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"The Obama campaign shoots back at talk","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"that any of those states may actually be in play .","depth":12},{"id":126,"text":"`` You see the Romney campaign and their allies heading into three states","depth":15},{"id":127,"text":"they are simply not going to win :","depth":15},{"id":128,"text":"Michigan , Pennsylvania , and Minnesota .","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"I am so confident of that ,","depth":14},{"id":130,"text":"that I 've put my mustache on the line , ''","depth":14},{"id":131,"text":"Axelrod said .","depth":12},{"id":132,"text":"But the Obama campaign is also putting up spots in those states ,","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"prompting the Romney camp to say","depth":13},{"id":134,"text":"the Obama campaign is playing defense .","depth":13},{"id":135,"text":"`` We feel like","depth":14},{"id":136,"text":"they 're defending territory","depth":15},{"id":137,"text":"while we 're on offense , ''","depth":15},{"id":138,"text":"Madden added .","depth":13},{"id":139,"text":"There 's been a heavy dose of state polls","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"released already this week ,","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"with many more","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"to come the rest of this week and into the final weekend before the election .","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"But as with the national polls , sometimes the numbers behind the state survey toplines are more revealing .","depth":6},{"id":144,"text":"`` In the battlegrounds , Obama 's running two very different campaigns","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"and he 's mobilizing two very different coalitions , ''","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"Brownstein said .","depth":7},{"id":147,"text":"`` In the Sun Belt states , the president 's putting most of his chips on cultural liberalism ,","depth":8},{"id":148,"text":"aimed mostly at younger voters , mainly white , college-educated white voters .","depth":8},{"id":149,"text":"But in the Rust Belt , Obama 's running better among blue-collar white voters due to his economic populism .","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"They are his last line of defense ,","depth":9},{"id":151,"text":"and he 's running significantly better among blue-collar white voters in Ohio , Wisconsin and Iowa than anywhere else . ''","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"But in the end , there 's only one number","depth":6},{"id":153,"text":"that will count .","depth":6},{"id":154,"text":"And that 's the number of electoral votes","depth":6},{"id":155,"text":"each ticket has won .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":311,"left":0,"right":310,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":310,"left":205,"right":309,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":205,"left":164,"right":204,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":158,"right":163,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":158,"left":1,"right":157,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":157,"left":2,"right":3,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":163,"left":159,"right":162,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":159,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent"